      "name": "Tool Calling",
      "description": "Defines how LLM function/tool calls are handled inside BotCompose.\n\n## Function / Tool Calling\n\nDevelopers can pass a list of tools to the LLM using `llm_tool_list`. The schema is similar to the JSON schema typically passed to LLM SDKs or Responses APIs, but simplified:\n- The `type` field is excluded and always treated as `function`.\n- If a function expects no arguments, the `parameters` schema can be omitted.\n\nThe `tool_manager` determines how tool calls are handled.\n\nBotCompose ships with a default tool manager named `default_tool_manager`.\n\n### Built-in Supported Tools\n- `drop_call`\n- `transfer_call`\n- `update_stt_config`\n- `update_llm_config`\n- `update_tts_config`\n\nThe update tools can dynamically modify the `plugin_data` of STT, LLM, and TTS plugins during the current call.\nThis allows runtime updates such as changing STT/TTS language or switching plugin models based on conversation flow.\n\n### Additional Tool Manager Configuration\nThe default tool manager also supports the following `plugin_data` fields:\n- `tool_url`\n- `tool_bearer_token`\n- `play_message`\n\nIf configured, when the LLM invokes any tool other than the built-in tools above, BotCompose:\n1. Starts playing the configured `play_message`\n2. Makes an HTTP `POST` request to `tool_url` in parallel\n3. Sends the tool payload defined below"
